betterquesting.name: Saplings
betterquesting.desc: You can craft a Sapling with Living Roots obtained from the big Roots sticking out of your island. To grow that Sapling, twerk or sprint around it and make sure it's not below the Mana Flare.

betterquesting.name: Logs
betterquesting.desc:
Trade in half a stack of Logs for 5 Log Chickens.

 Note: Shift+right-click on Chickens to carry them.

betterquesting.name: Cobble
betterquesting.desc: You can shift+right-click on Grass blocks or Dirt to obtain Pebbles with which you can craft Cobblestone

betterquesting.name: Tinker's Tables
betterquesting.desc: To make Tinker's Construct tools, you are going to need these "Tables".

betterquesting.name: Crushing
betterquesting.desc: With a Stone Hammer and Crushing Table, you'll be able to crush down certain blocks into other blocks. Simply right-click with the Hammer on the Crushing Table.

betterquesting.name: Flint
betterquesting.desc: You can crush Cobblestone down into Gravel, which you can then craft into Flint. Trade in 8 Flint for 5 Flint Chickens.

betterquesting.name: Sand
betterquesting.desc: You can crush Gravel down into Sand. Trade in 16 Sand for 5 Sand Chickens.

betterquesting.name: More Dyes
betterquesting.desc:
With Floral Fertilizer, you'll be able to obtain Mystical Flowers, which can be crafted into Petals and their Petals into Dyes.

 Note: By placing Petals on Grass blocks, using Bonemeal on them and shearing them, you can essentially obtain infinite Petals and Floral Dyes.

betterquesting.name: Henhouse
betterquesting.desc: Henhouses, at the cost of Hay Bales, collect the drops of nearby Chickens and make Dirt in the process.

betterquesting.name: A Small Farm
betterquesting.desc: Use the Bonemeal from the Bones, that you got from Skeletons, to grow Grass, break it to obtain Seeds and make a tiny Farm with them. You are going to need Seeds for breeding and growing Chickens faster and you are going to need Wheat for Dirt, in a way.

betterquesting.name: Bones
betterquesting.desc: Make a simple mob farm and kill a Skeleton. Don't worry if you get nothing from the Bone White Chicken Eggs as you'll be able to craft more after the next quest.

betterquesting.name: Analysing Chickens
betterquesting.desc: The Chicken Analyzer will allow you to see the stats of your Chickens.

betterquesting.name: Chicken Catcher
betterquesting.desc: The Chicken Catcher turns Chickens into items, allowing you to have more of them in your inventory and store them.

betterquesting.name: Petal Apothecary
betterquesting.desc: The Petal Apothecary will allow you to make certain Botania Flowers.

betterquesting.name: Pure Daisy
betterquesting.desc: The Pure Daisy can transmute Wood into Livingwood, Stone into Livingrock and a few more blocks into other blocks.

betterquesting.name: Mana Pool
betterquesting.desc: Mana Pool are used for storing Mana and using it for transmuting items.

betterquesting.name: Transferring Mana
betterquesting.desc: You can use Mana Spreaders for transferring Mana around. It can be rotated and can have Flowers bound to it with a Want of the Forest.

betterquesting.name: Alchemy Catalyst
betterquesting.desc: You can put an Alchemy Catalyst below a Mana Pool to be able to transmute even more items with Mana.

betterquesting.name: Alfheim Portal
betterquesting.desc: You can build a Portal to the Alfheim which uses Mana to transmute Mana items into their Elven versions.

betterquesting.name: Conjuration Catalyst
betterquesting.desc: When the Conjuration Catalyst is placed under a Mana Pool, it'll allow you to duplicate certain items with Mana.

betterquesting.name: The Gaia Guardian
betterquesting.desc: You can summon the Gaia Guardian with the structure given in the Lexica Botania.

betterquesting.name: Cursed Earth
betterquesting.desc: Cursed Earth quickly and passivly spawns monsters on top of it. Shift+right-click on an Enchanting Table to see how to make it.

betterquesting.name: Wither Skulls
betterquesting.desc: A Blood Infuser with a Promise of Tenacity III will allow you to make Wither Skeleton Skulls.

betterquesting.name: The Wither
betterquesting.desc: Now that you have Wither Skeleton Skulls, kill the Wither Boss.

betterquesting.name: The End?
betterquesting.desc: Craft an End Cake and fill it up with Eyes of Ender to be able to travel to the End.

betterquesting.name: Netherrack
betterquesting.desc: Netherrack cane be made in a Blood Infuser with a Promise of Tenacity II.

betterquesting.name: Chorus Fruit
betterquesting.desc: Travel to the outher islands of the End and obtain Chorus Fruit.

betterquesting.name: Less Messy Expansion
betterquesting.desc: Angel Blocks allow you to expand your base and make other platforms without having to make bridges.

betterquesting.name: The Cheapest Powered Furnace
betterquesting.desc: The Electric Furnace is the cheapest powered Furnace and the fastest, when it has 4 Overclocker Upgrades.

betterquesting.name: Basic Automation
betterquesting.desc: The Block Breaker, Placer and Activator do what you'd think they do.

betterquesting.name: Super Basic Automation
betterquesting.desc: The Super versions of the Activator, Breaker and Placer are faster and have an area of effect, but use RF.

betterquesting.name: Nests
betterquesting.desc: You can place any Egg in a Egg Nest, to make sure that a Chicken will hatch from it. You can even sit on top of it to make it faster.

betterquesting.name: Smart Chickens
betterquesting.desc: Give vanilla Chickens a Book to make them have stats and have their drops picked up by Henhouses.

betterquesting.name: Ranged Automatic Breeding
betterquesting.desc: By placing a Feeding Trough close to Chickens and filling it with Seeds, they will automatically breed when they can.

betterquesting.name: Quartz
betterquesting.desc: Now that you've made all the "basic" Chickens, you may take 5 Nether Quartz Chickens, which will allow you to make more advanced Chickens.

betterquesting.name: Roosts
betterquesting.desc: You can put Chickens in Roosts which will collect all their drops. Its speed depends on the amount of Chickens in it and their Gain.

betterquesting.name: Roost Collector
betterquesting.desc: If you don't like having a lot of piping, nor organizing, then the Roost Collector is the machine for you! It collects the items from Roosts in a 9x9 area around it.

betterquesting.name: One-Block Automatic Breeding
betterquesting.desc: You can put Chickens in a Chicken Breeder together with Seeds to automatically breed them. It's also faster than the regular breeding cooldown. Its speed depends on: the amount of Chickens in its slots (makes it faster), the Chickens' Growth (makes it faster) and the Chickens' Tier (makes it slower).

betterquesting.name: Worktable
betterquesting.desc: The Worktable allows you to switch between conflicting recipes and can remember 9 recipes.

betterquesting.name: I Like Bees
betterquesting.desc: By checking this off, you will unlock all the quests related to Bees.

betterquesting.name: I Don't Like Bees
betterquesting.desc: By checking this off, you hereby agree that you do not want to do anything with Bees and therefore will not unlock any quests that have anything to do with them.

betterquesting.name: Peat
betterquesting.desc: Put Bog Earth aroung Water and it'll eventually turn into Peat.

betterquesting.name: Manure
betterquesting.desc: With an Animal Net you can pick up Chickens and put them in a Nesting Pen. Nesting Pens work like Roosts, but you can only put 1 Chicken in them and unlike in Roosts, Chickens will generate Manure in them. It can be used for crafting Fertilized Dirt which is much better than regular Dirt.

betterquesting.name: Liquid Fertilizer
betterquesting.desc: You can make Liquid Fertilizer with Manure, Water and power in a Fertilizer Mixer. You can use it in a Fertelizer Sprayer for turning Dirt or Farmland into Fertilized Dirt or Farmland and for making crops grow faster.

betterquesting.name: Power From Fertilizer
betterquesting.desc: The Methane Digester Generator produces RF from Liquid Fertilizer

betterquesting.name: Separating Families
betterquesting.desc: The Nursery Monitor separates baby and adult Chickens.

betterquesting.name: Plastic From Feathers
betterquesting.desc: The Shredder allows you to turn Feathers into Feathers Fibers from which you can make a variety of things, including Plastic.

betterquesting.name: Lucky Eggs
betterquesting.desc: Lucky Eggs can be made in the Lucky Egg Machine and give you random vanilla items.

betterquesting.name: Immersive Tech
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Immersive Engineering and Immersive HempCraft.

betterquesting.name: Digital Storage
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Refined Storage, Refined Storage Addons and Storage Reborn.

betterquesting.name: Thermal Mods
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Thermal Foundation/Expansion/Dynamics, Redstone Arsenal, Funky Locomotion, Industrial Expansion and Whoosh.

betterquesting.name: Industrial Revolution
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Gadgetry, Industrial Foregoing and Industrial Meat.

betterquesting.name: Tinkering
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Tinker's Construct, Tinker's Complement, Tinnker I/O and PlusTIC.

betterquesting.name: Power Full
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Extreme Reactors, Zetta Industries, Energetic Sheep, Advanced Generators, Pressure Pipes and Solar Flux Reborn.

betterquesting.name: Advanced Resources
betterquesting.desc: This page starts with obtaining the Nether Quartz Chickens and ends with obtaining Chorus Fruit.

betterquesting.name: Actually Additions
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Actually Additions.

betterquesting.name: Mekanism
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Mekanism.

betterquesting.name: Calculator
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Calculator.

betterquesting.name: Botania
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Botania.

betterquesting.name: EvilCraft
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around EvilCraft.

betterquesting.name: Draconic Evolution
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Draconic Evolution.

betterquesting.name: Extra Utilities
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Extra Utilities.

betterquesting.name: A Builder's Life
betterquesting.desc: This page is based Better Builder's Wands, Chisel, Chisels and Bits and a bit of Exchangers and Xtones.

betterquesting.name: Helpful Technology
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Compact Machines and Psi.

betterquesting.name: Tech Reborn
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Tech Reborn.

betterquesting.name: Forestry
betterquesting.desc: This page is based around Forestry, Gendustry and Binnie's Mods.
